The paper discusses the application of neural machine translation for question parsing and query construction, which falls under the intersection of natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of templates for building alignments between questions and queries, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper references recent works in natural language generation, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG).
